                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, slightly irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; a few lines
                           and a group of lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page
                           of Text I; groups of lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit
                           page of Text II; initial line of Text III; incipits of sections/miracles;
                           name of the month “za-Maggābit” on fols. 3r-6r; word "salām" in Text III;
                           text dividers; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#97rb">97rb</locus> (incipit of Text III): simple coloured
                        (red) ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="99vb" to="100ra">ff. 99vb-100ra</locus>
                           <desc type="LandGrant">Note on bequething land to the church of Gabra Manfas
                              Qǝddus.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              የባለ፡ አገር፡ የነበረ፡
                              ገራህት፡ የጭቆች፡ ፊታውራሪ፡ ቢተው፡ ለአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ይሁን፡ ብለው፡ ሰጡት፡ በንቡረ፡ እድ፡
                              ተክለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ። ሹመ፡ ነጋሪት፡ ፊታውራሪ፡ ቢተው፡ ሊቀ፡ ካህናቱ፡ &lt;...&gt;፡ ወቄስ፡ ገበዝ፡
                              አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀስ[sic]፡ ዘተአገሎ፡ ለዝንቱ፡ ገራህት፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዘቲውህበ፡
                              በሰላጢን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic and Gǝʿǝz, by a mediocre hand.
                              Nǝbura ʾǝd Takla Giyorgis is mentioned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc> Signs, in the shape of a cross with a loop at the end of
                           each arm, are written in red or black in the side margins of <locus target="#10va">10va</locus>, 47rb, 58va, 67ra, 68va, 74ra. 
 - Pen
                           trials: <locus target="#100v">100v</locus>.</desc></item>
                           <item xml:id="e2"><desc> Minor notes, writing
                              exercises, doodles: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2r, 100rv.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings of Text I are indicated by the
                              names of the months written in the upper margin of some fols., by the
                              main hand: za-Maggābit: fols. 3ra, 4ra, 5rb-10rb za-Miyāzyā: fols.
                              10va, 11rb-14rb za-Gǝnbot: fols. 14vb, 16rb-22rb za-Sane: fols.
                              23rb-34rb za-Ḥamle: fols. 34vb, 36rb-40rb za-Naḥase: fols. 41ra,
                              42rb-45rb ba-Maskaram: fols. 46ra, 47rb-57rb za-Ṭǝqǝmt: fols. 58va,
                              60rb-62rb za-Ḫǝdār: fols. 63vb, 66rb-66rb za-Tāḥśāś: fols. 67ra, 68rb
                              za-Ṭǝrr: fols. 68vb, 69rb-73rb za-Yakkātit: <locus target="#74ra">fol.
                                 74ra</locus></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc type="findingAid"> - Monthly readings of Text II are indicated by the
                              names of the months written in the upper margin of some fols, by a
                              secondary crude hand: za-Miyāzyā: <locus target="#77ra">fol.
                                 77ra</locus> zä-Gǝnbot: <locus target="#79ra">fol. 79ra</locus>
                              za-Sane: <locus target="#80rb">fol. 80rb</locus> za-Ḥamle: <locus target="#81rb">fol. 81rb</locus> za-Naḥase: <locus target="#82va">fol. 82va</locus> 
                           za-Maskaram: <locus target="#85ra">fol.
                                 85ra</locus> za-Ṭǝqǝmt: <locus target="#85va">fol. 85va</locus>
                           za-Ḫǝdar: <locus target="#87rb">fol. 87rb</locus> za-Tāḥśāś: <locus target="#89va">fol. 89va</locus> za-Ṭǝrr: <locus target="#91vb">fol. 91vb</locus> za-Yakkātit: <locus target="#93ra">fol.
                              93ra</locus> za-Maggābit: <locus target="#93vb">fol.
                              93vb</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
